{
  "page": "Gonfaloniere",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <i><b>gonfaloniere</b></i> is an elected military official in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free City\">Free City</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Duties\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Duties</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Known_gonfalonieres\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known gonfalonieres</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Duties\">Duties</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Duties\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <i>gonfaloniere</i> is appointed by the people and <a href=\"/index.php/Magister\" title=\"Magister\">magisters</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>. During periods of <a href=\"/index.php/Election\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Election\">election</a>, the candidates often procure entertainment for the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">commons</a> and bribe the magisters to gain votes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The gonfaloniere is the leader of the Lysene <a href=\"/index.php/Army\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Army\">army</a> and can gain <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">wealth</a> and glory in case of military victory. This position is viewed as a stepping stone towards the office of <a href=\"/index.php/First_Magister\" title=\"First Magister\">First Magister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the aftermath of the deaths of <a href=\"/index.php/Lysandro_Rogare\" title=\"Lysandro Rogare\">Lysandro Rogare</a> and his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Drazenko_Rogare\" title=\"Drazenko Rogare\">Drazenko</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Lysene_Spring\" title=\"Lysene Spring\">Lysene Spring</a>, the <i>gonfaloniere</i> <a href=\"/index.php/Moreo_Dagareon\" title=\"Moreo Dagareon\">Moreo Dagareon</a> was slain by his own elite guards and <a href=\"/index.php/Torreo_Haen\" title=\"Torreo Haen\">Torreo Haen</a> was <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poisoned</a> after being named <a href=\"/index.php/First_Magister\" title=\"First Magister\">First Magister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Lysaro_Rogare\" title=\"Lysaro Rogare\">Lysaro Rogare</a>, Lysandro's son and heir, aspired to rule Lys and was elected <i>gonfaloniere</i> after bribing <a href=\"/index.php/Magisters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Magisters\">magisters</a> and entertaining commoners. Lysaro planned on sacking <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a> to increase his wealth and influence, and then use these resources to become First Magister of Lys. However, the bankruptcy of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rogare_Bank\" title=\"Rogare Bank\">Rogare Bank</a> put an end to Lysaro's ambitions and brought the downfall of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Rogare\" title=\"House Rogare\">his family</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_gonfalonieres\">Known gonfalonieres</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known gonfalonieres\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Moreo_Dagareon\" title=\"Moreo Dagareon\">Moreo Dagareon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lysaro_Rogare\" title=\"Lysaro Rogare\">Lysaro Rogare</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gonfaloniere\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Gonfaloniere\">Gonfaloniere</a></i> was an office in Italy during the Middle Ages and Renaissance.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Lysene Spring and the End of Regency.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403103611\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.027 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.048 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 516/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8707/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1764/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1045/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2208/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.52 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   40.254      1 -total\n 69.53%   27.990      1 Template:Italic_title\n 25.16%   10.129      5 Template:Ref\n 16.28%    6.555      5 Template:Ref/core\n  4.19%    1.687      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:26060-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403103611 and revision id 287245\n -->\n",
